file.name: test-api.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  title: Test-API
  description: Only used for testing purposes
  version: 1.0.0
paths:
  /test:
    get:
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Successful"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestData'
    post:
      requestBody:
        description: "TestData"
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestData'
      responses:
        204:
          description: "Successful"
  /test/pathParams/{param}:
    get:
      parameters:
        - in: path
          name: param
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestEnum'
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Successful"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestData'
  /test/query:
    get:
      parameters:
        - in: query
          name: param
          schema:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestEnum'
          required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Successful"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestData'
  /test/secured:
    get:
      security:
        - apiKey: []
      responses:
        200:
          description: "Successful"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/TestData'
components:
  schemas:
    TestEnum:
      type: string
      enum:
        - "value1"
        - "value2"
    TestData:
      required:
        - data
      type: object
      properties:
        data:
          type: string
          example: "test"
          description: "just a test"
  securitySchemes:
    apiKey:
      type: apiKey
      name: x-api-key
      in: header
